---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SOCIAL_LINKS } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="James Weatherhead â€” MD/PhD student at UTMB building AI tools for medicine.">
  <div class="about-container">

    <!-- ===== INTRO SECTION ===== -->
    <section class="about-hero">
      <div class="photo-wrapper">
        <img src="/james.jpeg" alt="James Weatherhead" class="photo" />
      </div>

      <h1 class="about-title">About</h1>

      <p class="about-lede">
        I'm James. I'm an MD/PhD student at the University of Texas Medical Branch, pursuing
        a PhD in experimental pathology in the automated science track.
      </p>

    </section>

    <!-- ===== WHAT I BUILD ===== -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <p>
        I work under Peter McCaffrey, MD, the Chief AI Officer at UTMB. My PhD research focuses
        on connecting BAA-compliant, HIPAA-compliant LLMs to live web search and tooling like
        PubMed MCP servers. The core question: how do you make HIPAA-compliant models as capable
        as frontier models without leaking PHI and breaking HIPAA?
      </p>

      <p>Some of what I've built:</p>

      <ul class="about-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Safe Search</strong>: a system that connects HIPAA-compliant LLMs to web search
          to bring back information safely, built using vector stores, ontologies, and OpenAI
          embedding-003-large. Presented at Perplexity AI headquarters in San Francisco.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>PubMed MCP server</strong>: a Model Context Protocol server for PubMed search.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Qualified Health custom GPT</strong>: a HIPAA-compliant GPT that receives PHI
          documents and identifies PHI using few-shot prompt examples. Built to speed up work for
          people in the Pathology department and DCLS students. They use it as a first-pass
          de-identification tool, then take that output to frontier models for patient information
          analysis.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/JamesWeatherhead/receipts" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">receipts</a>:
          one sub-agent per reference in your manuscript. Each sub-agent creates a markdown file
          comparing what you claimed the reference said versus what the reference actually said,
          with suggestions for how to change your language to accurately reflect the source. An npm
          package and Claude Code skill.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/JamesWeatherhead/ehrsh" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ehrsh</a>:
          structured FHIR queries via natural language.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/JamesWeatherhead/asq-phi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ASQ-PHI</a>:
          a published benchmark of 1,051 synthetic clinical queries with token-level PHI annotations.
          Published in <em>Data in Brief</em>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/JamesWeatherhead/VibeRad" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">VibeRad</a>:
          a DICOM viewer built on Google AI Studio and Gemini for radiology exploration. Submitted
          to the Google DeepMind Kaggle competition, awaiting results.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        In Summer 2025, I was an AI Researcher at <a href="https://www.thriveaihealth.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Thrive AI Health</a> in
        San Francisco. I've presented at Retool Summit and Perplexity AI HQ.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== BACKGROUND ===== -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <div class="section-marker"></div>

      <p>
        I was born in London and moved to South Africa at 13, attending Pretoria Boys High School,
        before coming to the United States on an NCAA tennis scholarship. PhD in experimental
        pathology, automated science track, expected March 2027. MD through 2029.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== PUBLICATIONS ===== -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <div class="section-marker"></div>

      <h2 class="section-heading">Publications</h2>

      <ul class="about-list">
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/JamesWeatherhead/asq-phi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ASQ-PHI: A Synthetic Benchmark for PHI Detection at the LLM Boundary</a>.
          Published in <em>Data in Brief</em>.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== GET IN TOUCH ===== -->
    <section class="about-contact">
      <h2 class="contact-heading">Get in touch</h2>

      <p class="contact-text">
        I'm always open to conversations about medical AI, agent systems, or interesting problems
        in healthcare. The best way to reach me is email.
      </p>

      <div class="contact-links">
        <a href={`mailto:${SOCIAL_LINKS.email}`} class="contact-link contact-link-email">
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <rect x="2" y="4" width="20" height="16" rx="2" />
